"the_sun_isn_t_at_the_shown_position" = "The sun isn\'t at the shown position";
"the_sun_isnt_at_the_shown_position_answer" = "This usually happens when the compass loses its accuracy. It can happen easily if you keep your phone in a casing.\nTo fix this, go to the calibration menu and follow the steps.\nIt works best to move the phone a lot around all axes which can also be done by waving it in an 8-figure and turning it around yourself.\n\nYou can also manually calibrate by clicking on the sun. This won\'t calibrate the internal compass, it will just move everything accordingly.\nYou should only do this if the compass is off by a constant factor but otherwise precise.";

"how_does_the_drawing_mode_work" = "How does the drawing mode work?";
"how_drawing_mode_works_answer" = "If you touch the drawing icon you\'ll enter drawing mode with new buttons.\n\nWhen you draw, the area between the horizon and your stroke is grayed out. This mode then tells you how many sun-hours or sun energy (kWh/m2) the gray area represents for a whole year.An example would be to draw an edge around a tree and see how many sun-hours or (kWh/m2) it would give to cut it down.\n\nThe freeze button freezes the camera and sensory input such that you don\'t need to hold your device still while drawing.\n\nYou can draw straight lines with the straight-line button.\n\nYou can also undo your last line by touching Undo or Clear everything to completely start over your drawing.\n \n You can switch the units to represent solar irradiance (kWh/m2) or sun hours in the menu under Settings. ";
"why_are_there_two_dates_at_the_top" = "Why are there two dates at the top?";
"two_dates_at_the_top_answer" = "The sun will be at any given point in the sky two times during the year, it shows both.\n\nYou can click either of the dates to set that as the current only date.";
